@startuml
!include ../includes/appsec-style.puml
title AppSec Process 11: SonarQube Quality + Security Gate (PR & Main)

' Purpose: Enforce clean-code and security quality gates early, without duplicating GHAS/Coverity.
'          SonarQube is the fast feedback loop; AppCode is the project key.

start

partition "Setup" {
  :Create SonarQube project (key = AppCode);
  :Select quality profile (language + security rules);
  :Configure PR decoration + branch analysis;
}

partition "Run in CI" {
  :CI runs SonarScanner;
  :Publish results to PR and dashboard;
}

partition "Quality Gate" {
  if (Quality gate passed?) then (Yes)
    :Allow PR to proceed;
  else (No)
    :Block merge<<gate>>;
    :Create/Update ticket (AppCode);
  endif
}

partition "Remediate" {
  :Fix issues (bugs, hotspots, vulnerabilities);
  :Re-run analysis until pass;
}

partition "Govern" {
  if (Exception needed?) then (Yes)
    :Time-boxed waiver + rationale;
    :Add compensating control;
  else (No)
    :No exception;
  endif
  :Track trends (new issues, debt) by AppCode;
}

note right
Key message: **Fast quality gates reduce rework**.
Use SonarQube for continuous hygiene; use GHAS/Coverity for deeper SAST.
end note

stop
@enduml
